'''Keith Shologan''' (born November 26, 1985 in [[Spruce Grove, Alberta]]) is a [[Canadian football]] [[defensive tackle]] for the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] of the [[Canadian Football League]]. He played [[college football]] at [[UCF Knights football|Central Florida]].

Shologan has also been a member of the [[San Diego Chargers]].

==Professional career==
===Saskatchewan Roughriders===
Shologan was considered a top pick in the [[2008 CFL Draft]] and a possible pick of the [[Edmonton Eskimos]] along with [[Dimitri Tsoumpas]] and [[Samuel Giguere]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://slam.canoe.ca/Slam/Football/CFL/Edmonton/2008/04/29/5418731-sun.html|title=Draft-day options|last=Huntington|first=Jonathan|date=April 29, 2008|publisher=Slam Sports|accessdate=2009-06-26}}</ref> However Shologan signed with the [[San Diego Chargers]]. He attended the Chargers training camp however he was cut. He joined the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] in week eight after they drafted him with the fourth pick in the 2008 draft.<ref name="Riders">{{cite news|url=http://www.saskriders.com/team/roster/detail/?roster_id=324|title=#74 Keith Shologan|publisher=Saskatchewan Roughriders|accessdate=2009-06-26}}</ref> He appeared in one game as a backup defensive lineman with Saskatchewan and didn't record a stat.<ref name="Riders" />

==Personal==
Shologan lives on a [[bull]] farm with his family in Northern [[Alberta]] during the offseason and he enjoys playing [[squash]] in his spare time.<ref name="Riders" />

